The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Dishnet rolls out broadband

 A STAFF REPORTER

 Calcutta, June 25: The Chennai-based Dishnet Wireless Limited (DWL) has launched its wireless broadband services, Red, in the city. 

 We shall set up 6,000 WiFi (wireless fidelity) hotspots in 34 locations across the country. In the first phase, we plan to offer wireless services in eight big cities in the country at an investment of Rs 275 crore, said V. G. Suri, sales and marketing vice-president of the Rs 850-crore company. He added, The revenues generated in the first phase will provide for investment in the second phase.

 About 400 WiFi hotspots across the country are already in various stages of installation. The company expects to create 500 WiFi areas by July-end. For Calcutta, it has identified 70 locations and the figure might go up to over 250 within a year.

 Suri said both Calcutta and Mumbai were expected to contribute Rs 14 crore each in the first twelve months of operations. 




